docs.lead_paragraph: U.S. Environmental Protection Agency chief Gina McCarthy ordered some top staff members in late September to focus on lead contamination in Flint, Michigan — after university researchers and local doctors warned that city residents were in danger — and said the matter "could get very big very quickly," according to emails released Wednesday.
